.C.<br><br>Son of John Ames Belden, and of Clara Belden, of Edmonton, Alberta, Canada.</p></div><div><p class='name'>Flight Sergeant JAMES BELL</p><p>August 02, 1943<br>Royal Canadian Air Force<br><br>Son of John and Jane Bell. Husband of Martha Martina Bell, of Edmonton, Alberta.</p></div><div><p class='name'>Pilot Officer JOHN BELL</p><p>March 22, 1944<br>Royal Canadian Air Force<br><br>Son of John and Ida A. Bell, of Edmonton, Alberta, Canada.</p></div><div><p class='name'>Private WILLIAM HENRY BELL</p><p>July 08, 1944<br>Canadian Scottish Regiment, R.C.I.C.<br><br>Son of William Henry and Priscilla Bell, of Edmonton, Alberta.</p></div><div><p class='name'>Private WILLIAM MACDONALD BENBOW</p><p>February 10, 1945<br>Calgary Highlanders, R.C.I.C.<br><br>Son of Lewis and Lovis Benbow, of Edmonton, AB; Husband of Margaret Joan Benbow, of Edmonton.</p></div><div><p class='name'>Captain JOHN GREGORY BENEDICT</p><p>July 07, 1988<br>408 Tactical Helicopter Squadron<br><br>Son of John Benedict of Tasis, British Columbia and Sandra Lee Doerkson of Munster Hamlet, Ontario.  Brother of Andrew and Michael.  Husband of Captain Marie Pier Elizabeth Mirielle (nee Cloutier) Benedict of St. Albert, Alberta.
